WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.885
Typically, regulation
of payment systems

2
00:00:03.885 --> 00:00:07.140
focuses principally
on issues of first,

3
00:00:07.140 --> 00:00:10.469
fairness, by disallowing
certain practices

4
00:00:10.469 --> 00:00:13.110
that feel unfair or abusive.

5
00:00:13.110 --> 00:00:16.950
Issues of transparency,
by making the fees

6
00:00:16.950 --> 00:00:18.750
and rates associated with credit

7
00:00:18.750 --> 00:00:20.715
and debit cards more transparent,

8
00:00:20.715 --> 00:00:23.625
so consumers understand how
much they're actually paying,

9
00:00:23.625 --> 00:00:25.860
and consumers understand how

10
00:00:25.860 --> 00:00:28.155
much merchants are
actually getting.

11
00:00:28.155 --> 00:00:30.255
Issues of overall risk,

12
00:00:30.255 --> 00:00:32.160
by ensuring that for example,

13
00:00:32.160 --> 00:00:35.880
consumer credit is
appropriately allocated so that

14
00:00:35.880 --> 00:00:37.860
systemic risk of

15
00:00:37.860 --> 00:00:41.910
overall financial crisis
