20
00:00:51.740 --> 00:00:55.225
transparency, and systemic risks
that we've discussed.

21
00:00:55.225 --> 00:00:57.820
With respect to debit cards,

22
00:00:57.820 --> 00:01:00.290
in the decade leading up
to the financial crisis,

23
00:01:00.290 --> 00:01:02.420
the fastest growing source
of revenue for

24
00:01:02.420 --> 00:01:05.165
financial institutions was from

25
00:01:05.165 --> 00:01:07.910
fees that they collected
from their customers.

26
00:01:07.910 --> 00:01:10.279
These fees included for example,

27
00:01:10.279 --> 00:01:13.280
overdraft fees that are
charged to consumers

28
00:01:13.280 --> 00:01:17.490
who unwittingly overdraw
on their accounts.

29
00:01:17.490 --> 00:01:20.735
When overdraft was first
introduced as a product,

30
00:01:20.735 --> 00:01:24.380
the way that banks decided
whether they would complete

31
00:01:24.380 --> 00:01:28.370
the transaction and charge
consumers an overdraft fee,

32
00:01:28.370 --> 00:01:31.440
or decline the
transaction and simply

33
00:01:31.440 --> 00:01:32.975
refuse to let it be

