00:01:32.975 --> 00:01:35.360
processed with this
payment instrument,

35
00:01:35.360 --> 00:01:37.040
was on a case-by-case basis

36
00:01:37.040 --> 00:01:39.320
determined by the nature
of the consumer

37
00:01:39.320 --> 00:01:41.300
that they were dealing
with and also the nature

38
00:01:41.300 --> 00:01:43.780
and size of the
transaction itself.

39
00:01:43.780 --> 00:01:46.190
In the decade leading
up to the crisis,

40
00:01:46.190 --> 00:01:48.535
what banks realized
with the help of

41
00:01:48.535 --> 00:01:51.175
third-party vendors who
emerged in this space,

42
00:01:51.175 --> 00:01:52.700
was that, overdraft could be

43
00:01:52.700 --> 00:01:54.560
a really profitable
revenue source

44
00:01:54.560 --> 00:01:56.435
for financial institutions.

45
00:01:56.435 --> 00:01:58.970
If they instead of discouraging

46
00:01:58.970 --> 00:02:01.610
consumers from relying on
overdraft for example,

47
00:02:01.610 --> 00:02:03.350
by in some instances declining

48
00:02:03.350 --> 00:02:06.650
these transactions or on
a case-by-case basis,

49
00:02:06.650 --> 00:02:10.370
instead encouraging consumers
to turn to overdraft as

50
00:02:10.370 --> 00:02:12.980
a product with a series of

51
00:02:12.980 --> 00:02:16.430
practices that we now think
of as rather nefarious.

52
00:02:16.430 --> 00:02:18.440
For example, what became

53
00:02:18.440 --> 00:02:22.355
commonplace in the period
leading up to the crisis,

54
00:02:22.355 --> 00:02:24.305
was for banks to order

55
00:02:24.305 --> 00:02:26.300
your transactions in
a way that made it

56
00:02:26.300 --> 00:02:30.305
most likely for you to incur
the maximal overdraft fees.

57
00:02:30.305 --> 00:02:32.030
For example, imagine that

58
00:02:32.030 --> 00:02:34.040
you wake up in
the morning and you're

59
00:02:34.040 --> 00:02:35.600
the kind of consumer who tends to

60
00:02:35.600 --> 00:02:38.380
transact with your debit card
with some frequency.

61
00:02:38.380 --> 00:02:41.530
You start the day with $10
in your checking account,

62
00:02:41.530 --> 00:02:44.665
and you go to Starbucks
