in their checking accounts.

107
00:04:42.985 --> 00:04:45.700
Concerned about
overdraft as a practice,

108
00:04:45.700 --> 00:04:48.710
also related to the fact
that people simply did not

109
00:04:48.710 --> 00:04:50.120
realize that they were about to

110
00:04:50.120 --> 00:04:52.935
overdraw and bear
these expensive fees.

111
00:04:52.935 --> 00:04:56.060
Around 70 percent of customers
who were surveyed reported

112
00:04:56.060 --> 00:04:59.120
that they wish that these
transactions had been declined,

113
00:04:59.120 --> 00:05:02.320
rather than completed with
the significant overdraft fee.

114
00:05:02.320 --> 00:05:04.700
In response, what
regulators chose

115
00:05:04.700 --> 00:05:06.995
to do in the aftermath
of the crisis,

116
00:05:06.995 --> 00:05:10.040
was change the default
rules around overdraft.

117
00:05:10.040 --> 00:05:11.780
Prior to the financial crisis,

118
00:05:11.780 --> 00:05:13.835
100 percent of consumers
were basically

119
00:05:13.835 --> 00:05:17.150
automatically opted into
overdraft protection,

120
00:05:17.150 --> 00:05:20.075
as it is referred to
again rather ironically,

121
00:05:20.075 --> 00:05:22.730
which means that they're
eligible for incurring

122
00:05:22.730 --> 00:05:25.160
