transaction that they had made.

150
00:06:50.710 --> 00:06:54.230
Concerned observers of
the debit card industry

151
00:06:54.230 --> 00:06:56.120
and overdraft in particular,

152
00:06:56.120 --> 00:06:57.795
suggests that the new opt in

153
00:06:57.795 --> 00:07:00.305
rules haven't actually
gone far enough.

154
00:07:00.305 --> 00:07:01.610
This is a point made by

155
00:07:01.610 --> 00:07:04.100
legal academics
like Lauren Willis,

156
00:07:04.100 --> 00:07:06.335
Ryan Bubb, and Richard Pildes.

157
00:07:06.335 --> 00:07:09.880
These academics point out that,

158
00:07:09.880 --> 00:07:12.335
if you look to see
the consumers who have

159
00:07:12.335 --> 00:07:16.010
